description:
The FunctionBuilder emit loop appears 4 times with identical structure:
  make_context -> set signature -> FunctionBuilder::new -> build body -> finalize -> define_function -> clear_context

FOUR SITES (all in compile_with_backend):
  lines ~1633-1660: fz_main_entry
  lines ~1670-1742: fz_spawn_entry
  lines ~1751-1782: fz_resume_park
  lines ~1807-1832: fz_halt_cont_body_*

EXTRACT helper (near top of file, generic over Module):
  fn emit_fn_body<M: cranelift_module::Module>(
      module: &mut M,
      fbctx: &mut FunctionBuilderContext,
      sig: Signature,
      func_id: FuncId,
      f: impl FnOnce(&mut FunctionBuilder<'_>),
  ) -> Result<(), cranelift_module::ModuleError> {
      let mut ctx = module.make_context();
      ctx.func.signature = sig;
      {
          let mut b = FunctionBuilder::new(&mut ctx.func, fbctx);
          f(&mut b);
          b.finalize();
      }
      module.define_function(func_id, &mut ctx)?;
      module.clear_context(&mut ctx);
      Ok(())
  }

Replace the 4 boilerplate sites with calls to emit_fn_body.
The 5th occurrence (line ~2835, user fn compilation) wraps compile_fn differently — leave it.

cargo build must produce zero warnings. All tests must pass.
